# SECTION 4: STRUCTURAL DIAGRAMS & SCHEMATICS

## 4.1 Diagram 1 — Node Anatomy (Block-Level Architecture)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    nodePrev[Previous Pointer - prev] -->|points to| structNode
    structNode[DLL Node]
    nodeData[Data Field - int data] --> structNode
    nodeNext[Next Pointer - next] -->|points to| structNode
    structNode -->|outputs| fieldA[Address of predecessor]
    structNode -->|outputs| fieldB[Stored integer value]
    structNode -->|outputs| fieldC[Address of successor]
```

## 4.2 Diagram 2 — Doubly Linked List Traversal Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    N1["Node 1 - Data 10 - Prev NULL Next Node2"] -->|next| N2["Node 2 - Data 20 - Prev Node1 Next Node3"]
    N2 -->|next| N3["Node 3 - Data 30 - Prev Node2 Next Node4"]
    N3 -->|next| N4["Node 4 - Data 40 - Prev Node3 Next NULL"]
    N4 -->|prev| N3
    N3 -->|prev| N2
    N2 -->|prev| N1
    HEAD((HEAD pointer)) --> N1
    TAIL((TAIL pointer)) --> N4
```

> **Reading the diagram:** Solid arrows `next` flow left-to-right (forward traversal); arrows `prev` flow right-to-left (backward traversal). `HEAD` enters at Node 1, `TAIL` points to Node 4.

## 4.3 Diagram 3 — Insertion Operation Flowchart (Middle Insertion)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    start([Start: Insert node N after node A]) --> locate[Step 1 - Traverse list to find node A]
    locate --> found{A found in list?}
    found -->|No| errfail[Return error - A not present]
    found -->|Yes| identify[Step 2 - Let B = A.next]
    identify --> step1[Step 3 - N.next = B]
    step1 --> step2[Step 4 - N.prev = A]
    step2 --> step3[Step 5 - B.prev = N]
    step3 --> step4[Step 6 - A.next = N]
    step4 --> endop([End: Node N inserted between A and B])
```

## 4.4 Diagram 4 — Deletion Operation Flowchart (Middle Deletion)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    startD([Start: Delete node N between A and B]) --> locateD[Step 1 - Locate node N with given value]
    locateD --> checkfound{N found?}
    checkfound -->|No| errmsg[Return - value not in list]
    checkfound -->|Yes| getneighbors[Step 2 - Set A = N.prev and B = N.next]
    getneighbors --> updA[Step 3 - If A exists - A.next = B]
    updA --> updB[Step 4 - If B exists - B.prev = A]
    updB --> freenode[Step 5 - free N to release memory]
    freenode --> finishD([End: Node N removed from list])
```

## 4.5 Diagram 5 — Memory Block Layout (Pointer Directionality Map)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    H[[HEAD]] -->|stores address of| A1["Node 0 - addr 1000"]
    A1 -->|prev field 992| X1[NULL]
    A1 -->|data field 996| D1[Value 10]
    A1 -->|next field 1004| A2["Node 1 - addr 2000"]
    A2 -->|prev field 1992| A1
    A2 -->|data field 1996| D2[Value 20]
    A2 -->|next field 2004| A3["Node 2 - addr 3000"]
    A3 -->|prev field 2992| A2
    A3 -->|data field 2996| D3[Value 30]
    A3 -->|next field 3004| X2[NULL]
    T[[TAIL]] -->|stores address of| A3
```

> **Caption:** This diagram illustrates the scattered (non-contiguous) memory allocation of DLL nodes. Each node occupies a **24-byte block** (8 bytes for `int`, 8 bytes each for two pointers on a 64-bit machine). The `HEAD` and `TAIL` are external pointers maintained by the programmer.

